reviews.review: Oh it's bad. REALLY bad. It's also ironically one of the most enjoyable movies of the year. In the beginning you'll be scratching your head at the confusing or ridiculous  but things happening on the screen. Halfway through I was literally sitting on the edge of my seat just waiting for the next laugh out  loud or impossible thing to happen. (It's borderline endless!) If you have small kids or want to have a good laugh with friends it's absolutely worth a watch
great experience....fun...a few tears....few laughter. Smooth way to End the Saga.

This movie in my opinion is the best one out of the three new movies. It has a few flaws but I don't think it would have had as many flaws if they didn't have to spend time making up for past movie mistakes.
It’s not perfect. It couldn’t be. It won’t satisfy every question, and will start a few new ones. It does, however, provide a fun, fast paced thrill ride of an experience from beginning to end.
Most epic Star Wars yet. Loved it from beginning to end.

I have to say I really appreciate this course correction since it apparent that while Johnson got Luke, Kylo aspect of the story right in Last Jedi, he truly messed up on Snoke/Palpatine, Rey and Finn's character narratives. Now, JJ has come back, course-corrected to what he originally had planned for these core characters. I'm glad that my suspicions were right with Rey, Snoke, and above all Finn being force sensitive. However, its obvious the first half of the film was what Last Jedi was supposed to be, and the later half the final fight with Rey and Ben. 

This needed either another movie or at 45 minutes more to explore more of what occurred post Last Jedi. But in all, I'm happy with the film. Cried in some sequences especially towards the middle half when everything is revealed to Rey and what occurs to Leia in the process of that revelation. 

Go watch it, don't let the Last Jedi shills tell you otherwise.
I loved everything about it. It tied up all the loose ends perfectly !  I will see it again, probably two or three more times ...
Go to criticize, and you will. Go to enjoy, and you will love it. You choose how to view.  Personally I loved all three sequel movies... and I’d rather enjoy my time than spend it criticizing.
I really enjoyed the movie.  It is good fast paced, star wars fun.
